README

how to build:

make clean
make server
make client

how to start:

./server
./client


~HELP~
To use this client you have to add the IP and the Port as parameter.
For example:
 ./client -i 127.0.0.1 -p 7777

All options:
# -i ... IP address
# -p ... Port
# -h ... Help
# -f ... read from file

If you do not set any IP or port, default values (ipconf.h) will be used.

Special commands:
 ~logout~ ... client will disconnect and terminate.



implemented features:
client logout: ~logout~
ipv4,ipv6 and hostname support
file read in


